article_title: Anthem Profits Tumble On Higher Obamacare Costs

article_metadata.description: Anthem surprised Wall Street this morning with news its fourth-quarter profits fell 64% as the company was hit with higher than-expected medical expenses in its individual health insurance business, which includes plans offered on public exchanges under the Affordable Care Act. The large health insurer, which operates Blue Cross and Blue Shield [...]
